'''Gold Coast Airport''', or '''Coolangatta Airport''', {{airport codes|OOL|YBCG}} is an Australian domestic and international airport on the [[Gold Coast, Queensland|Gold Coast]] and is located some {{convert|100|km|abbr=on}} south of [[Brisbane]] and 25&nbsp;km south of Surfers Paradise. The entrance to the airport is situated in the suburb of [[Bilinga, Queensland|Bilinga]] on the Gold Coast. The runway itself straddles 5 suburbs of twin cities across the state border of [[Queensland]] and [[New South Wales]]. During summer these states are in two different time zones.

Gold Coast Airport is currently the sixth busiest international airport in Australia and the 3rd fastest growing airport in the country.<ref>{{cite web|title=About Gold Coast Airport|url=http://goldcoastairport.com.au/corporate/about-gold-coast-airport/|publisher=Gold Coast Airport|accessdate=13 April 2011}}</ref>

==History==
