|Virgin Australia operated by [[Pacific Blue Airlines|Pacific Blue]]|Auckland | 1
}}

===Cargo services===
The following airlines operate scheduled cargo flights from Gold Coast Airport. All cargo services operate from the Freight Terminal.

{{airport-dest-list
|[[Toll Priority]] operated by [[Toll Aviation]] |Ballina, Bankstown, Brisbane, Coffs Harbour
}}

[[Australian air Express]] uses the belly space of Jetstar aircraft to transport cargo domestically. It is also contracted for Jetstar international flights and Air New Zealand flights from the airport. It offers same day/overnight and standby services domestically airport to airport and airport to door from Gold Coast Airport.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goldcoastairport.com.au/at-the-airport/general-aviation-freight/ |title=General Aviation & Freight |publisher=Gold Coast Airport |accessdate=30 May 2011}}</ref>

[http://www.coastcargo.com.au Coast Cargo] offers a full range of international and domestic logistics services at Gold Coast Airport. As a privately owned, IATA-accredited freight forwarder Coast Cargo provides both inbound and outbound freight services on all airlines at Gold Coast and Brisbane Airports. At Gold Coast Airport, Coast Cargo provides numerous services including courier, international and domestic pet animal transport services on Virgin Blue and Pacific Blue airlines, line-haul services Gold Coast to Brisbane and international and domestic freight services.<ref>{{cite web|title=Coast Cargo - About Us|url=www.coastcargo.com.au|work=Coast Cargo - Gold Coast International Airport Air Freight|accessdate=6 September 2011}}</ref>

Coast Cargo is a registered Cargo Terminal Operator (CTO) and currently handles Air Asia X, Pacific Blue and Virgin Blue airlines. It is also the agent for Toll Air Express.<ref>{{cite web|title=General Aviation and Freight|url=http://goldcoastairport.com.au/at-the-airport/general-aviation-freight/|work=Gold Coast Airport - At the Airport|publisher=Gold Coast Airport|accessdate=6 September 2011}}</ref>

