==Bus Connections==
[[File:302frnt.png|150px|right|thumb|[[Surfside Buslines]]]]
2 local bus routes service the Gold Coast Airport.
BUS CARD:
*<span style="color:#0d6cb6;">
Buy a Bus pass card if you are staying longer than five (5) days, becuase the trips work out to be cheeper. But the card will cost you $5 dollars plus you need to recharge it $20 would be a good start.
TIME:
*<span style="color:#0d6cb6;">

DO NOT FORGET IF YOU LIVE IN SOUTHERN STATES THAT THE AIRPORT RUNS ON QUEENSLAND TIME. EVEN THOUGH THE AIRPORT IS IN NSW. SO ALWAYS USE GOLD COAST TIME. 

Both of these are operated 7 days by [[Surfside Buslines]]

Northbound:
*<span style="color:#0d6cb6;">'''702 <U+2013> Southport'''</span> via Gold Coast Highway <U+2013> Palm Beach, Burleigh Heads, Broadbeach, Surfers Paradise, Australia Fair
*<span style="color:#0d6cb6;">'''761 <U+2013> Varsity Lakes Rail'''</span> <U+2013> via The Pines and then express to Varsity Lakes

Southbound:
*<span style="color:#0d6cb6;">'''761 <U+2013> Tweed Heads'''</span> via Kirra and Coolangatta

